One in five NSW families have admitted to sedating their children before a long road trip . 
  The antihistamine Phenergan is commonly used to treat allergies but can cause breathing problems in young children . 
  A national driving survey revealed four in five families use technology to entertain their children . 
  Almost 20 per cent of NSW families admit to using sedatives to knock their children out . 
  The medical community claim the sedative should not be used on children as it can be fatal . 
 